{"duration":"1ms","environment":"development","level":"debug","message":"Prisma Query","params":"[\"🧩 Example Problem\n\n“Given an array of integers, find the length of the longest subarray with no repeating elements.”\n\n1. 🧠 Approach\n\nA brute-force way would be:\n\nGenerate all subarrays\nCheck each for duplicates\nTrack the max length\n\nThat works… but it’s painfully slow.\n\nBetter Idea: Sliding Window\n\nWe use:\n\nA window (two pointers: left and right)\nA Set (or Map) to track seen elements\nSteps:\nStart with both pointers at 0\nExpand right pointer:\nIf element is not in set, add it and update max length\nIf it is in set, shrink window from left until duplicate is removed\nContinue until right reaches the end\",\"2026-04-28 20:32:58.486 UTC\",\"Solid answer. You covered the main shape of the problem and gave enough detail to continue deeper.\",66,false,\"2c616d48-05f2-4be0-8956-a2dc3c94b596\"]","query":"UPDATE \"public\".\"interview_questions\" SET \"user_answer\" = $1, \"answer_submitted_at\" = $2, \"ai_evaluation\" = $3, \"score\" = $4, \"follow_up_needed\" = $5 WHERE (\"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"id\" = $6 AND 1=1) RETURNING \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"id\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"interview_session_id\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"question_id\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"question_text\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"question_type\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"expected_topics\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"user_answer\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"answer_submitted_at\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"ai_evaluation\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"score\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"follow_up_needed\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"question_order\", \"public\".\"interview_questions\".\"created_at\"","service":"interview-prep-api","timestamp":"2026-04-28T20:32:58.490Z"}
