{"duration":"0ms","environment":"development","level":"debug","message":"Prisma Query","params":"[\"\n\nSomil Choudhary\n+91 8010506506|somil2005@gmail.com|linkedin.com/in/somil-choudhary|github.com/somil0701\nEducation\nIndian Institute of Technology MadrasChennai, Tamil Nadu\nBachelor of Science in Data Science and ApplicationsMay. 2023 – Present\nGuru Gobind Singh Indraprastha UniversityDwarka, Delhi\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science and EngineeringAug. 2023 – Present\nExperience\nVirtual Software Developer InternApr 2024 – May 2024\nAccenture Nordics (Virtual Experience via Forage)New Delhi, India\n•\nCompleted a virtual developer simulation focused on gathering technical requirements and proposing cloud\nmigration strategies.\n•\nPracticed software development fundamentals including code comprehension, debugging, unit testing, and UAT.\n•\nGained exposure to security assessments, IAM policy implementation, and secure SDLC practices.\nTech Team Volunteer, Hack & Chill 2.0March 2025\nOrganizing CommitteeRemote\n•\nContributed to front-end development of the official hackathon website using ReactJS.\n•\nBuilt responsive navbar, footer, track section, and collaborated on the hero section UI.\nProjects\nQuiz Master V1|Jinja2, Bootstrap, Flask, SQLAlchemy, Matplotlib, SQLite3, VimApril 2025\n•\nDeveloped ”Quiz Master,” a multi-user exam preparation platform using Flask backend, Jinja2 templating, and\nBootstrap frontend, demonstrating full-stack development capabilities.\n•\nImplemented comprehensive user management with differentiated admin/user roles, SQLite database integration,\nand secure authentication workflows.\n•\nEngineered core functionalities including dynamic quiz creation, timed assessments, MCQ management, and\nperformance tracking across multiple subjects and chapters .\n•\nCreated an intuitive dashboard interface with summary charts and search capabilities, ensuring seamless user\nexperience for both administrators and exam participants .\nReact-Jobs|ReactJS, TailwindCSS, ViteJS, JSON, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScriptApril 2024\n•\nDeveloped a Full-Stack Job Management System:  Built a dynamic web application using React and Tailwind CSS\nfor the frontend and a JSON server for the backend, enabling users to perform CRUD operations on job listings.\n•\nImplemented Interactive Forms and Pages:  Created user-friendly forms and pages to add, edit, and delete job\npostings, ensuring a seamless user experience with real-time data updates.\n•\nHandled State Management and API Integration:  Managed application state efficiently using React hooks and\nintegrated with a JSON server to fetch and manipulate job data, demonstrating proficiency in asynchronous\noperations and RESTful APIs.\nTechnical Skills\nLanguages:  JavaScript, Python, C/C++, Java, Bash\nFrameworks:  MongoDB, ExpressJS, ReactJS, NodeJS, Tailwind CSS, BootStrap, Flask, Matplotlib, Jinja2,\nPostgreSQL, SQLite3\nDeveloper Tools:  Git, Postman, Google Cloud Platform, VS Code, Vim, Linux, Zsh, Terminal Emulators\nDesign:  Figma, Excalidraw, Adobe Photoshop, GIMP\nExtra Curricular Activities\n•Developed ”Tourisma” at DTU Vihaan 007 Hackathon:  Participated in a Major League Hacking (MLH) sponsored\nevent, creating an intermediary platform connecting tourists with tour guides, akin to Swiggy and Ola.\n•Solved 700+ DSA Questions on different coding platforms such asLeetCode, GeeksforGeeks,Codeforces, etc.\n•Achieved a peak rating of1557+onLeetCodeand 1189+ onCodeforces\n•Have a strong understanding of Data Structures and Algorithms\",{\"summary\":\"Somil Choudhary\\n+91 8010506506|somil2005@gmail.com|linkedin.com/in/somil-choudhary|github.com/somil0701\\nEducation\\nIndian Institute of Technology MadrasChennai, Tamil Nadu\\nBachelor of Science in Data Science and ApplicationsMay. 2023 – Prese\",\"experience\":[],\"education\":[],\"projects\":[],\"skills\":[\"JavaScript\",\"React\",\"PostgreSQL\",\"Python\"]},[{\"skillName\":\"JavaScript\",\"confidenceScore\":0.